{
  "text": "There was no dierence in the amplitude or concentration dependence of a,b-meATP evoked contractions between mice +/+ and +/7 for the P2X 1 receptor (the pEC 50 values were 5.39+0.09 and 5.31+0.04 respectively, n=7 \u00b1 8, Figure 4a ). This indicates that like for the vas deferens [CITATION_1] only one copy of the P2X 1 receptor gene is required for normal expression of P2X receptors in bladder smooth muscle. The peak amplitude of contractions to a maximal concentration of carbachol were the same for +/+, +/7 and 7/7 mice (4.3+0.5, 4.4+0.4 and 4.5+0.3 respectively) and so data have been normalized to the response to the maximal carbachol response. In the bladder the maximal response and pEC 50 for carbachol is the same for +/+, +/ 7 and 7/7 mice (pEC 50 s of 5.07+0.14, 5.4+0.09 and 5.28+0.09 respectively, n=4 \u00b1 10 Figure 4b ) demonstrating that the lack of contraction to purinergic agonists of the 7/ 7 mouse bladder is not due to an eect on contractile function. In addition to the lack of eect on contractions to carbachol there was no obvious dierence in bladder size or function between +/+ and 7/7 mice indicating that the P2X 1 receptor de\u00aeciency had no eect on the development or morphology of the bladder, and as reported previously there is no obvious eect of the P2X 1 receptor de\u00aeciency on bladder \u00aelling [CITATION_2] .",
